WorldStage NewsOnline— The Nigeria Police Force (NPF) has confirmed the withdrawal of its personnel from Very Important Personalities (VIPs) in the country ahead of the Saturday’s elections. Police spokesman, Frank Mba disclosed this while responding to questions on a national TV station on Friday. Mba said the withdrawal became necessary for the force to deploy more personnel for the elections, for the purpose of providing security for the Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) officials, observers and voters.